            <h1>How It Works</h1>

            <div class="howto-left">
              <ul>
                <li><h4>Potential deliverers register and define their (commuter-) route(s) and tolerable deviation radius.</h4></li>
                <li><h4>A customer buys a product in the e-shop and starts a delivery request at Deliverado. He/ She also specifies a delivery time slot.</h4></li>
                <li><h4>Registered deliverers receive a notification (depending on their set routes and radius) and can decide whether to accept the order.</h4></li>
                <li><h4>The app should also allow a chat between the deliverer and the customer (e.g. to agree on a different time slot).</h4></li>
                <li><h4>Upon delivery, the customer signs on the phone or tablet of the deliverer to confirm receipt.</h4></li>
                <li><h4>Incentives for deliverers provided through financial compensation, bonus system, coupons, social networks linkage, badges ("gamification"), etc. ...</h4></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
